            "questionText": "A marine research submarine uses optical fibres for deep-sea data transmission. The fibre core is made of glass with a refractive index of $!$n_1 = 1.50$!$ and is surrounded by cladding with a refractive index of $!$n_2 = 1.30$!$. Calculate the critical angle (in degrees) for light traveling from the core to the cladding for total internal reflection.",
